      • getUserNoIDP

        protected User getUserNoIDP​(javax.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest request,
                            javax.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse response,
                            UserMultiID userMultiKey)
                     throws IOException
        Finds the most recently created user with a specific UserMultiID.

        Nota Bene

        This should always work and return a unique user. SAML requires that the entity ID (aka dip parameter) restricts the domain of multi-id (So no matter what the IDP lists, say umissouri vs mizzou, no other institution can create an eppn with those domains.) If they should ever change that, then this might not work right. Unlikely, but this contract is implicit and necessary.
        Parameters:
        request -
        response -
        userMultiKey -
        Returns:
        Throws:
        IOException

      • getUserWithIDP

        protected void getUserWithIDP​(javax.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest request,
                              javax.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse response,
                              UserMultiID userMultiKey,
                              String idp)
                       throws IOException
        Legacy code. This does all the logic for users who have their IDP sent. Note that this uniquely identifies a user in the system, unlike the no IDP case. It will also make very complex logic decisions about whether the user's serial string needs to be changed -- a requirement for X509 certificates.

        DO NOT TOUCH

        ... without great probity first...
